  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (8478c08 2022-05-05T00:16:27.013152+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (amd)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen starting an Anvil process and deploying an account, I can see that it works via the Anvil logs:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nListening on 127.0.0.1:8545\r\nweb3_clientVersion\r\nweb3_clientVersion\r\nweb3_clientVersion\r\nweb3_clientVersion\r\neth_getTransactionCount\r\neth_chainId\r\neth_getBlockByNumber\r\neth_chainId\r\neth_estimateGas\r\neth_getBalance\r\neth_sendRawTransaction\r\n\r\n    Transaction: 0x0e8acfd5dab0ea8b32df29e03af939065abc1e3548b8eb2655fe1345d02bc783\r\n    Contract created: 0x274b028b03a250ca03644e6c578d81f019ee1323\r\n    Gas used: 496448\r\n    Block Number: 1\r\n    Block Hash: 0xf1d7024b6e913c99189035849952d8433be991e364e57ed96881e611e78ec97a\r\n    Block Time: \"Thu, 05 May 2022 19:01:40 +0000\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nNotice the part that says **    Contract created: 0x274b028b03a250ca03644e6c578d81f019ee1323**\r\n\r\nI then try to use `eth_getCode` in Postman to see if I can get the contract's code.\r\nHere is my request JSON:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getCode\",\"params\":[\"0x274b028b03a250ca03644e6c578d81f019ee1323\", \"latest\"],\"id\":0}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is the result:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n    \"id\": 0,\r\n    \"result\": \"0x\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n**NOTE: When I repeat all of these steps but using `npx hardhat node`, things work as expected**.",
